<paragraph pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
This plant is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. meridionalis" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">C. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except that it has considerably wider leaves that are silvery-lepidote on the lower surface and turn dark blackish green on the upper surface when dried. Further study is needed to determine if it should be recognized as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
